    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-07-24T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-07-24T04:00:00-05:00" n="596"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d596">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.00/2225: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Straus</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-07-24T10:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 24, 1936—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 24—6:17 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>637. Following message by telephone from Barcelona: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“July 24, 9 a.m. Death of Clerk Iturralde confirmed. Body brought to
                            Barcelona by authorities last night. His companion, British subject,
                            also killed at same time. Death of Iturralde deeply felt as he died
                            endeavoring to protect Americans. Served this Consulate faithfully 17
                            years. Leaves family and four children penniless. Local authorities have
                            expressed concern, sympathy and regret Franklin.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Straus</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
